<TITLE> Football won't be affected, minister assures Salahuddin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 25 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Football Federation president Kazi Salahuddin said the sports minister had assured him that football would not be affected by the government's decision to stage the 2011 Cricket World Cup opening ceremony at the Bangabandhu National Stadium. The BFF high-ups sat with sports minister Ahad Ali Sarker on Wednesday, a day after the minister made that announcement. Salahuddin along with BFF senior vice-president Salam Murshedi and vice-president Badal Roy met Sarker at his ministry. "Football will not be affected by the opening ceremony of the World Cup as no one wants to hamper it Football is a popular game in the country," Salahuddin quoted Sarker as saying. The BFF supremo said they had reached a consensus on how to find a solution. "I hope we will be able to reach a decision in a couple of days after a meeting between all concerned parties," said the legendary football. bd
